    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and finely dice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced carrot[s]</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[455ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[595ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leeks have softened, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock, chopped potatoes </strong>and your<strong> creamy single soy</strong> and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are almost fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced pollock </strong>(unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) and <strong>spinach</strong> to the potatoes and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-8 min or until the pollock is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender \u2013 this is your <strong>curried pollock, leek & potato chowder</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-pollock-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried pollock, leek & potato chowder</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
